{
  "uuid": "a8bacceb5e76ff1cc10a7ac72df6a98e",
  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Administrative Assistant",
  "description": "<p>We’re an agile, early-stage aircon servicing company based in Singapore, committed to delivering top-quality solutions. As we scale, we're seeking an adaptable and proactive Administrative Assistant to be the backbone of our operations—someone who thrives in a fast-paced startup, wears multiple hats, and helps drive our success every day.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><u><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></u></p>\n<p>- Provide general office administration: answer calls/emails/WhatsApp messages, Customer relationship Management (CRM), and handle correspondence. </p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>- Schedule and coordinate appointments, service calls, deliveries, and technician dispatches. </p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>- Prepare and manage quotations, job sheets, invoices, receipts, and maintain accurate records of sales, payments, and outstanding balances. </p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>- Oversee office supplies, documentation, filing systems, and vendor coordination. </p>\n<p>Support procurement of aircon parts and liaise with suppliers and internal teams. </p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>- Maintain up-to-date leave records for staff, oversee approvals, and ensure accurate documentation of absences and team availability.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>- Develop and prepare contractual agreements for new workers.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><u><strong>Ideal Candidate Profile</strong></u></p>\n<p>- Diploma in Business Administration, Office Management, or equivalent.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>- 1–3 years of experience in an administrative or operations role—preferably within same industry or equivalent.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>- Basic knowledge in Microsoft Office (Excel, Word, Outlook)</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>- Strong organizational skills, attention to detail, and ability to multitask in a fast-moving environment.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>- Excellent written and verbal communication skills in English—capable of corresponding with customers, technicians, and suppliers.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>- Self-starter mindset, adaptable, and capable of working independently with minimal guidance.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><u><strong>Nice-to-Haves</strong></u></p>\n<p>- Experience with basic bookkeeping or invoicing tasks. </p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>- Startup experience or willingness to jump in wherever needed with a “do-whatever-it-takes” attitude.</p>\n<p>Bilingual ability (e.g., English + Mandarin/Malay/Tamil) depending on customer base.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><u><strong>What We Offer</strong></u></p>\n<p>A dynamic startup environment with opportunity to grow into operations or office management roles.</p>\n<p>Clear visibility into business operations and direct impact on company efficiencies.</p>\n<p>Supportive team culture that values initiative, flexibility, and collaborative problem-solving.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><u><strong>Work Schedule &amp; Workplace</strong></u></p>\n<p>This role is fully onsite, comprising 5.5 days per week (including a half‑day on Saturday)</p>\n<p>Monday to Friday 9:00 AM to 6:00 PM.</p>\n<p>Half‑day on Saturday 9:00 AM to 1:00 PM</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>Location: 39 Woodlands Close </p>",
